RACE CONDITION\
\
\
\
INTRINSIC LOCK\
- is on a per object basis and not on a per method basis, so when a method is synchronized it is actually working on the objects lock\
- a thread can enter an objects unsynchronized methods even if another thread holds the lock of the object\
- static synchronized methods use Class object as the lock (since there is no instance variable involved)\
- pessimistic locking\
- lock is also known as monitor\
\
\
The way to use synchronization is either to use synchronize(object) \
OR \
use the \'91synchronized\'92 modifier on the objects method\
\
\
IMPORTANT: When a thread synchronizes on an object it means that the thread has acquired a lock on the object\
\
\
synchronization = mutual exclusion (only one thread holds the lock) + reliable thread communication\
synchronization is considered a bit expensive in processing because threads that dont have a lock on an object need to be suspended (BLOCKED STATE) and resumed (RUNNABLE then RUNNING) when lock is available\
\
Synchronization rules\
- in a class add synchronize to every method in which the variable you want to protect is accessed\
- use same lock to guard the same shared mutable variable, don\'92t use a different lock (so synchronized method of one object  and synchronized block of another object in the same class)\
- if a method modifies a static field you must use synchronize access to this field even if the method is typically used only by a single thread\
- keep a synchronized block small\
- try to move time consuming activities out of synchronized blocks without affecting thread safety\
- avoid excessive synchronization\
\
Note: StringBuffer uses synchronization but is mostly used by a single thread. Therefore replaced with StringBuilder\
\
A thread in synchronized block can be context switched\
\
\
\
VOLATILE VARIABLES\
- a volatile variable lives in main memory and not in CPU cache (remember that there could be many CPU\'92s each with its own cache)\
- it is read from main memory and not from CPU cache\
- writes are to main memory and not to CPU cache\
- volatile keyword guarantees visibility of changes to variables across threads\
\
\
Locking (synchronization) VS Volatile (volatile) - locking can guarantee both visibility and mutual exclusion (atomicity) while volatile variables can only guarantee visibility\
\
\
\
\
ATOMIC VARIABLES\
- applies to single variables that are \
	Scalars\
	Arrays\
	Field Updaters\
	Compound Variables\
- package is java.util.concurrent.atomic.*\
- provides memory visibility between threads\
- provides atomicity on a variable [meaning all operations in sequence on a variable (read, update, write) are run together as one indivisible unit that cannot be affected by a race condition]\
- thread safety\
- they are regarded as \'91better volatile variables\'92\
- the underlying implementation uses a non-blocking algorithm/optimistic locking\
\
\
\
\
\
THREAD COOPERATION \
\
Using Volatile\
\
\
Using wait() & notify()\
- when a thread goes into waiting via wait() it releases the lock on an object\
- notify() method wakes other thread from waiting state and the other thread moves to blocked state [lock on the object is not released at notify(), but rather at end of synchronized block OR at the call of wait()]\
- to go from blocked state to runnable state a thread needs to acquire the lock on an object, no lock on object no progress to runnable\
- use wait() method inside a while loop, why? Sometimes a thread can have a spurious wakeup, i.e. it is woken up from wait() state even when it did not receive a notify from another cooperating thread, in this case the while loop helps\
\
Concurrency utilities\
\
\
Note: sleep() and yield() will not release the lock on an object\
\
\
\
THREAD INTERRUPTION\
\
Java provides a cooperative mechanism for requesting a thread to stop what it is doing\
Every thread has a boolean - interrupted status which is false by default\
Thread blocked due to stream IO is uninterruptable	- the stream needs to be closed to interrupt the thread\
Threads blocked due to intrinsic locks (obtained via synchronize) are also uninterruptable\
\
\
\
\
